| Notes                   = * The animated film ''Marvel's Hulk: Where Monsters Dwell'' was announced at San Diego Comic-Con 2016. Marvel's staffers promised the feature will be more "adult-oriented" than Marvel's animated series currently on Disney XD, comparing it to the [[wikipedia:DC Universe Animated Original Movies|animated movies]] based on DC Comics.{{cite|ref=true|url=http://www.newsarama.com/30366-marvel-s-secret-wars-gets-animated.html|title=SECRET WARS & CIVIL WAR Animated Series, HULK Movie, GUARDIANS OF GALAXY Renewed by MARVEL ANIMATION|last=Arrant|first=Chris|work=Newsarama|date=24 July 2016|accessdate=8 October 2016}}
* The film premiered at New York Comic Con 2016.
* Despite not having any critic reviews on Rotten Tomatoes, the film possesses a 63% of audience approval score, with an average rating of 2.5/5.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/marvels_hulk_where_monsters_dwell|title=Marvel's Hulk: Where Monsters Dwell (2016) Rotten Tomatoes|work=Rotten Tomatoes|accessdate=18 March 2018}}
| Trivia                  = * The subtitle for this film is based after the comic series {{cl|Where Monsters Dwell Vol 1}}.
